        {
            "_id": "oDlnUYRNJcOhEpyW",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Distracting Whispers",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A gale frenzy can focus all of their whispered words in a cacophony of unsettling and distracting threats, lies, and taunts, assaulting the minds of those they target with the plethora of distinct sounds. The gale frenzy selects one creature within 90 feet and fills its mind with these wind-borne distractions. The targeted creature must attempt a @Check[will|dc:28|options:damaging-effect] save with the following results. The gale frenzy can't use Distracting Whispers again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Distracting Whispers]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[10d6[mental]] damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} for 1 minute.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "air",
                        "auditory",
                        "mental",
                        "primal"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "PHJY6fpXJwMmdm5F",
